-- Russian Equity Movers: Gazprom Neft, Polymetal Move in Moscow
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-06-25T11:29:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/russian-equity-movers-gazprom-neft-polymetal-move-in-moscow.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 1.2
percent to 1,331.58 by 3:05 p.m. in Moscow, the fourth day of
declines and the longest losing streak in almost seven weeks.
The dollar-denominated RTS Index retreated 1.2 percent to
1,266.58.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX) advanced 1.8 percent to 144.05
rubles, the highest level since April 25 on a closing basis. The
stock climbed on speculation the oil arm of  Russia ’s natural gas
exporter won’t buy BP Plc’s stake in TNK-BP.  Polymetal International Plc (POLY)   climbed 1.5 percent
to 927 pence, the most on an intraday basis since June 20.
 Petropavlovsk Plc (POG)   rose 2.3 percent in  London  to 465.70
pence, gaining for the first day in four. Nomura International
Plc upgraded the Russian precious metals producers, citing lower
valuations.  -- Editors: Ash Kumar, Linda Shen  To contact the reporter on this story:
